  },
  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I hope your walk after lunch helped — even a short one can feel like a reset. How are you feeling today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I’m feeling good, thank you. The walk helped a bit. I like walking in the afternoon. Helps me relax. By the way, did you watch any good movie recently? Maybe something Bollywood?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Good to hear the walk helped — afternoon walks are the best for winding down. I haven’t watched a movie recently, but I love Bollywood! Drama or action today?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I prefer drama movies, to be honest. Action can get too loud for me. There was this one movie last year, *Dilwale*, with Shah Ruaah... I think? It was okay, but not my favorite. Have you seen it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said it perfectly — *Dilwale* is a big movie, and it's fun to talk about. I liked it for the music and the big family scenes. What part stood out for you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The music was good, definitely. There was one song that played during a festival scene — very colorful and lively. But the story felt a bit too long for me. I kept waiting for it to get better, but it never really did. Maybe I should try a different genre next time. Any suggestions?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said that clearly — I get it, long stories can drag. Sometimes a lighter film helps. What about *Raees*? It has some nice drama and action balance. Or a comedy?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, *Raees*... I think I heard some mixed things about it. Maybe I’ll try the comedy route instead? I like a good laugh sometimes. Do you know any good Bollywood comedies that aren't too old? Something from the last few years?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it — comedy is the way to go. *Chhichhore* is fun and recent, or *Pati Patni Aur Woh* if you like some drama with the laughs. Ever tried either?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I haven’t seen *Pati Patni Aur Woh*, but *Chhichhore* sounds interesting. I’ll check it out. Thanks for the suggestion! Btw, how do you usually relax after work? Do you prefer movies or something else?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You’re welcome — I hope you enjoy it! After work, I’m a big fan of tea and quiet walks. Even 20 minutes outside feels like a reset. What’s your go-to unwind?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Tea and walks sound nice, really. I sometimes prefer just lying down and scrolling mindlessly — not the best, I know. Maybe I should try your way. It’s getting late, though. I should wrap up. Talk to you soon!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said that clearly — small steps matter. Quiet walks do wonders, but rest is rest. Talk soon, Priyansh — tell me how *Chhichhore* is if you try it!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Sure thing! I'll let you know if I watch it. Have a great evening, Maya! 🌅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You’re welcome — I hope your evening is calm and warm. Tell me how you like *Chhichhore* if you try it. Good night, Priyansh!"
    }
  ],
